$touch_1 = array(
   'title'=>'Problem',
   'data'=>'For our final project in the ubiquitous computing course, my teammate and I decided to 
   investigate how current technologies could be enhanced to better support the social interactions 
   of families separated by distance.  In order to answer this question, we first had to understand 
   how adult children who have moved to a different city make use of existing technologies to 
   interact with their families.',
   'images'=>array(
     '1'=>'touch/problem.jpg'
   )
);
   
$touch_2 = array(
   'title'=>'The Ethnographic Approach',
   'data'=>'We wanted to collect real data about these long distance interactions including information 
   such as the date and time of the interactions, the medium used for the interactions, the content of the 
   conversations, and how the interactions were initiated.  As such, we decided to ask our participants to 
   keep a diary of each interaction over a 2 week period in order to collect in-situ data.  An additional 
   benefit of the diary method was that it would sensitize our participants to the topic under study and 
   reduce the recall bias during the debriefing semi-structured interview.  Since we collected the diaries 
   before the interviews, we were able to analyze the data for patterns and narrow the focus of the interview questions.',
   'images'=>array(
      '1'=>'touch/diary.jpg',
   )
);

$touch_3 = array(
   'title'=>'Organizing the Raw Data',
   'data'=>'An affinity diagram was developed using the data collected from the interviews.  We noticed many 
   emergent themes that we had not previously anticipated including issues of availability, awareness, and forgetfulness.',
   'images'=>array(
      '1'=>'touch/affinity.jpg'
   )
);

$touch_4 = array(
   'title'=>'A Vision for the Future',
   'data' => 'We discovered that there are many potential ways in which existing technologies could be enhanced to support 
   the social interactions of families separated by distance and include some of the following ideas:
      <ul>
      <li>Prompts based on time or content that reminds users to initiate an interaction with a family member.</li>
      <li>Facilitate a user’s awareness of a loved one’s availability.  This could entail integration of calendaring 
      functionality with instant messaging services or using physical sensors placed around a house to detect a 
      loved one’s presence in a ‘communication available’ zone.</li>
      <li>Seamless integration of various communication platforms including messaging, 
      phone, email such that a loved one’s availability is always evident.</li>
   </ul>'
);

